1. Izgleda da je propast projekta neizbežna. (*propast*) (It seems that the failure of the project is inevitable.)
2. Kompanija je propala zbog lošeg upravljanja. (propala) (The company went bankrupt due to poor management.)
3. Njihov brak je propao zbog stalnih svađa. (propao) (Their marriage failed due to constant arguments.)
4. Nadamo se da neće biti propasti u planiranom putovanju. (*propasti*) (We hope there won't be any mishaps in the planned trip.)
5. Velika poplava je dovela do propasti malih preduzeća. (*propasti*) (The major flood led to the collapse of small businesses.)
6. Da bi izbegli propast, moramo hitno promeniti strategiju. (*propast*) (To avoid failure, we need to urgently change our strategy.)
7. Njegovo zdravlje je u propasti zbog dugotrajnog zanemarivanja. (*propasti*) (His health is in ruins due to long-term neglect.)
8. Od ovog projekta zavisi budućnost naše kompanije, ne smemo dozvoliti propast. (*propast*) (The future of our company depends on this project, we cannot allow failure.)
9. Bez velike promene u politici, država će završiti u propasti. (*propasti*) (Without a major change in policy, the state will end up in ruin.)
10. Kada je saznala za propast svog omiljenog restorana, bila je veoma tužna. (*propast*) (When she found out about the demise of her favorite restaurant, she was very sad.)